  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want a consistent transaction UI so that I can easily make and understand transactions from both Wallet and Chat.\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want a send tokens in chat.\r\n\r\nAs a developer, I don't want to duplicate UI's and flows so that I can have cleaner code.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Improvement\r\n\r\nSending and receiving transactions should be a consistent experience (easier for both users, designers, and developers), but currently, there are different screens and flows when initiating from Wallet or a chat. We can easily fix this to streamline transactions and UX as users don't need to learn 2 UI's and see redundant screens, and developers don't need to maintain it.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nConsistent and delightful transaction flows\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nInconsistent transaction flows. \r\nUsers have complained in Instabug about slider UI.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"169\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-04-26 at 11 54 13 am\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/116099/39299421-f4b8848e-4948-11e8-85b6-4d3d6b9cf983.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n[comment]: # (Please summarise the solution and provide a task list on what needs to be fixed.)\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\nA consistent flow from both wallet and chat screens (note screenshot if for illustration purposes)\r\n<img width=\"636\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-04-26 at 11 32 20 am\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/116099/39299435-fb682028-4948-11e8-8769-a63fa94afdce.png\">\r\n\r\nFrom wallet, flow is unchanged.\r\nFor chat, a user can invoke the transaction screen by doing:\r\n```\r\n/send \r\n/send 100\r\n/send 100 SNT\r\n/send 100 ETH\r\n```\r\nThe wallet screen is prefilled with the recipient, and amount/asset if it was entered. The slider screen is skipped.\r\n\r\n### Additional\r\n\r\nThis flow would fix https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/2923 by allowing tokens to be sent in chats.",
